Explanation:
- The app registers a blueprint with url_prefix="/cms" in app.create_app -> register_blueprints (app/__init__.py).
- In app/api/cms/__init__.py the cms blueprint registers the user blueprint with url_prefix="/user".
- In app/api/cms/user.py the register endpoint is declared with @user_api.route("/register", methods=["POST"]). Combining the prefixes yields the full path /cms + /user + /register â†’ /cms/user/register.
- The route decorator explicitly specifies methods=["POST"], so only POST is accepted according to the source code. (Per your instruction I did not assume implicit framework behavior such as automatic OPTIONS/HEAD handling.)
